☁️ Major Cloud Providers

The three leading cloud providers dominate the market, each with their own strengths.

---

AWS (Amazon Web Services)

- Owned by Amazon
- Launched in 2006 — the oldest and most widely adopted cloud platform
- Largest market share in the cloud industry
- Key services: EC2 (virtual machines), S3 (storage), IAM, Lambda (serverless)
- Used by: Netflix, NASA, Airbnb

🏆 Best for: enterprises, startups, and cloud security roles (most job listings ask for AWS experience)

---

Microsoft Azure

- Owned by Microsoft
- Launched in 2010
- Second largest cloud provider
- Key services: Azure AD (identity), Virtual Machines, Blob Storage, Azure Security Center
- Used by: LinkedIn, Xbox, many enterprise and government organizations

🏆 Best for: companies already using Microsoft products (Windows, Office 365)

---

GCP (Google Cloud Platform)

- Owned by Google
- Launched in 2011
- Third largest cloud provider
- Key services: Compute Engine, Cloud Storage, BigQuery, Google Kubernetes Engine
- Used by: Spotify, Twitter, PayPal

🏆 Best for: data analytics, machine learning, and Kubernetes workloads

